<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ910906-0026</DOCNO><DOCID>910906-0026.</DOCID><HL>   Business Brief -- TECO Energy Inc.:   Tampa Electric Subsidiary   To Build $400 Million Plant</HL><DATE>09/06/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION</SO><CO>   TE</CO><MS>UTILITIES (UTI)</MS><IN>ELECTRIC UTILITIES (ELC)</IN><GV>ENERGY DEPARTMENT (ERG)</GV><RE>FLORIDA (FL)NORTH AMERICA (NME)UNITED STATES (US)</RE><LP>   TECO Energy Inc., Tampa, Fla., said its primarysubsidiary, Tampa Electric Co., will build a $400 millionpower plant in central Florida.   The 220 megawatt facility, according to company officials,will be the first to use so-called clean coal gasification, aprocess that combines coal gasification, gas turbine andsteam turbine technology. The project, the company said, willbe about 10% to 12% more efficient than conventional coalplants and will yield savings of $155 million over theprojected 20-year life of the plant.</LP><TEXT>   The U.S. Department of Energy has agreed to provide $120million for the project through the federal Clean CoalTechnology Program, established in the mid1980s.   When the plant is completed in 1996, it will serve 460,000customers in four central Florida counties covering about2,000 square miles.</TEXT></DOC>